openjdk:17.0.1-jdk-slim eclipse-temurin:17 why this are working and that one not explain in brief
Here is the exact brief explanation why:

✅ Why openjdk:17 Failed but openjdk:17.0.1-jdk-slim and eclipse-temurin:17 Worked
Reason 1 — openjdk:17 image DOES NOT EXIST on Docker Hub anymore
Docker Hub removed many old openjdk:* tags.
✔ openjdk:17.0.1-jdk-slim exists
❌ openjdk:17 does NOT exist (returns "not found")
So Kubernetes cannot pull it → ErrImagePull.

✅ Reason 2 — Architecture Support Differences (x86 vs ARM)
AWS EKS worker nodes = ARM64 or x86_64
✔ Working images (multi-arch)
	• openjdk:17.0.1-jdk-slim
	• eclipse-temurin:17
➡ These images support both x86_64 and ARM64.
❌ Failing image (missing ARM64 build)
	• openjdk:17
➡ Does NOT have ARM64 support, only x86_64 (and the tag was removed).
So containerd on ARM node cannot pull it.

📌 Simple Reason Summary (One-Line)
openjdk:17 tag doesn’t exist and doesn’t support ARM64.
The other images exist AND support multiple architectures, so they work.

