MySQL StatefulSet in Kubernetes (Scalable & Production-Style)
A StatefulSet is used for stateful applications like MySQL, where:
	• Each replica needs its own persistent volume
	• Each pod gets a stable network identity
	• Data must not be lost if pods restart
	• Scaling should create new DB replicas safely

⭐ Architecture Overview
Components:
	1. Headless Service → Provides stable DNS for MySQL pods
	2. StatefulSet → Creates mysql-0, mysql-1, mysql-2
	3. PersistentVolumeClaim Template → Gives each pod its own disk
	4. ConfigMap (optional) → Custom MySQL configuration



apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: StatefulSet
metadata: 
  name: my-sts 
spec: 
  serviceName: mysql-service   # Required for StatefulSet
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: mysql
  replicas: 5
  template: 
    metadata:
      labels: 
        app: mysql
    spec: 
      containers:
        - name: mysql
          image: mysql:8
          ports:
            - containerPort: 3306
          env:
            - name: MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD
              value: redhat123

